                <h2>Position Attributes</h2>
                <p>
                Click the grey rectangle (id <i>floater</i>) to change its position.
                <p>
                Changing the position of the rectangle will toggle its css <i>float</i> attribute and its text content.
                <p>
                <div id="position-holder">
                    <div id="floater">
                        Click to<br/>
                        float right
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h2>Size Attributes</h2>
                <p>
                Use the slider to change the size of the apple.
                <p>
                The slider handle itself is an anchor with a css class of <i>ui-slider-handle</i>. It changes
                the <i>height</i> attribute in the image with an id of <i>apple</i> and a src of <i>../images/apple.jpg</i>.
                <div id="slider-holder">
                    <div id="slider"></div>
                </div>
                
                <div id="size-holder">
                    <div id="current-size">Current size <span id="height-value">150</span>px</div>
                    <img id="apple" src="../images/apple.jpg"/>
                </div>               
                
